    "id": "source-fullstack-docker-git-ci-cd-deployment-basics",
    "domain": "DevOps",
    "title": "Docker, Git, CI/CD, Deployment Basics",
    "summary": "Docker, Git, CI/CD, Deployment Basics Git workflow Good commit messages explain why, not just what. Pull request checklist - Does code solve the right problem? - Are edge cases handled? - Are errors meaningful? - Are tests added? - Are secrets avoided? - Are l...",
    "sourceFiles": [
      "full_stack_interview_prep_deep_chatgpt_style_v2(1).html"
    ],
    "content": "# Docker, Git, CI/CD, Deployment Basics\n\n## Git workflow\n\n```bash\ngit checkout -b feature/user-auth\ngit add .\ngit commit -m \"Add JWT auth flow\"\ngit push origin feature/user-auth\n```\n\nGood commit messages explain why, not just what.\n\n## Pull request checklist\n\n- Does code solve the right problem?\n- Are edge cases handled?\n- Are errors meaningful?\n- Are tests added?\n- Are secrets avoided?\n- Are logs useful but not leaking sensitive data?\n- Does DB migration have rollback/safety plan?\n\n## Dockerfile for FastAPI\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM python:3.12-slim\n\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY requirements.txt .\nRUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n\nCOPY . .\nCMD [\"uvicorn\", \"main:app\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", \"8000\"]\n```\n\n## Dockerfile for React build\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM node:22-alpine AS build\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY package*.json ./\nRUN npm ci\nCOPY . .\nRUN npm run build\n\nFROM nginx:alpine\nCOPY --from=build /app/dist /usr/share/nginx/html\n```\n\n## docker-compose\n\n```yaml\nservices:\n  api:\n    build: ./api\n    ports:\n      - \"8000:8000\"\n    environment:\n      DATABASE_URL: postgresql://postgres:postgres@db:5432/app\n    depends_on:\n      - db\n\n  db:\n    image: postgres:16\n    environment:\n      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: postgres\n      POSTGRES_DB: app\n    ports:\n      - \"5432:5432\"\n```\n\n## CI pipeline stages\n\n```text\ncheckout\n  → install dependencies\n  → lint\n  → type-check\n  → unit tests\n  → build\n  → docker image\n  → deploy to staging\n  → smoke tests\n  → deploy production\n```\n\n## Environment variables\n\nNever commit secrets.\n\n```bash\nDATABASE_URL=...\nJWT_SECRET=...\nREDIS_URL=...\n```\n\n## Deployment concepts\n\n| Concept | Meaning |\n| --- | --- |\n| blue-green deploy | switch traffic between two environments |\n| rolling deploy | replace instances gradually |\n| rollback | revert to previous version |\n| health check | endpoint/platform check to see app health |\n| migration | DB schema change |\n| smoke test | quick production sanity test |\n\n## Interview questions\n\n**Q: What should be in CI?**\n\nLinting, formatting, type-checking, tests, build, security checks, Docker image build, and deployment gates.\n\n**Q: How do you deploy DB migrations safely?**\n\nUse backward-compatible migrations: add nullable column first, deploy app writing both old/new if needed, backfill data, then enforce constraints/drop old column later.",
    "searchText": "devops docker, git, ci/cd, deployment basics docker, git, ci/cd, deployment basics git workflow good commit messages explain why, not just what. pull request checklist - does code solve the right problem? - are edge cases handled? - are errors meaningful? - are tests added? - are secrets avoided? - are l... # docker, git, ci/cd, deployment basics ## git workflow ```bash git checkout -b feature/user-auth git add . git commit -m \"add jwt auth flow\" git push origin feature/user-auth ``` good commit messages explain why, not just what. ## pull request checklist - does code solve the right problem? - are edge cases handled? - are errors meaningful? - are tests added? - are secrets avoided? - are logs useful but not leaking sensitive data? - does db migration have rollback/safety plan? ## dockerfile for fastapi ```dockerfile from python:3.12-slim workdir /app copy requirements.txt . run pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt copy . . cmd [\"uvicorn\", \"main:app\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", \"8000\"] ``` ## dockerfile for react build ```dockerfile from node:22-alpine as build workdir /app copy package*.json ./ run npm ci copy . . run npm run build from nginx:alpine copy --from=build /app/dist /usr/share/nginx/html ``` ## docker-compose ```yaml services: api: build: ./api ports: - \"8000:8000\" environment: database_url: postgresql://postgres:postgres@db:5432/app depends_on: - db db: image: postgres:16 environment: postgres_password: postgres postgres_db: app ports: - \"5432:5432\" ``` ## ci pipeline stages ```text checkout → install dependencies → lint → type-check → unit tests → build → docker image → deploy to staging → smoke tests → deploy production ``` ## environment variables never commit secrets. ```bash database_url=... jwt_secret=... redis_url=... ``` ## deployment concepts | concept | meaning | | --- | --- | | blue-green deploy | switch traffic between two environments | | rolling deploy | replace instances gradually | | rollback | revert to previous version | | health check | endpoint/platform check to see app health | | migration | db schema change | | smoke test | quick production sanity test | ## interview questions **q: what should be in ci?** linting, formatting, type-checking, tests, build, security checks, docker image build, and deployment gates. **q: how do you deploy db migrations safely?** use backward-compatible migrations: add nullable column first, deploy app writing both old/new if needed, backfill data, then enforce constraints/drop old column later."
