    "content": "# Mini Projects to Prepare for This JD\n\nBuild these in order. They directly match the job description.\n\n## Project 1: Authenticated Task Manager\n\nStack:\n\n- React + TypeScript\n- Redux Toolkit or RTK Query\n- FastAPI or Flask\n- PostgreSQL\n- JWT + refresh token cookie\n\nFeatures:\n\n- signup/login/logout\n- create/update/delete tasks\n- protected routes\n- pagination\n- search/debounce\n- role-based route\n\nWhat to explain:\n\n```text\nReact form → API validation → DB insert → JWT auth → protected route → Redux state update\n```\n\n## Project 2: Webhook Receiver\n\nFeatures:\n\n- `/webhooks/payment-provider`\n- signature verification\n- raw event storage\n- idempotency by event ID\n- queue processing\n- status update\n\nWhat to explain:\n\n```text\nWebhook should respond quickly. Actual work happens async. Duplicate events are safe.\n```\n\n## Project 3: Queue-Based Notification System\n\nStack:\n\n- Redis/BullMQ if Node\n- Redis Queue/Celery/RQ if Python\n\nFeatures:\n\n- enqueue email/SMS job\n- retry with exponential backoff\n- failed jobs page\n- idempotent worker\n\n## Project 4: Analytics Dashboard\n\nStack:\n\n- MongoDB aggregation or PostgreSQL group queries\n- React charts/table\n\nFeatures:\n\n- filters\n- aggregation by status/date/user\n- indexes\n- explain query before/after index\n\n## Project 5: Full System Design README\n\nWrite one README where you explain:\n\n- architecture diagram\n- API endpoints\n- DB schema\n- auth flow\n- queue flow\n- deployment plan\n- debugging plan\n- tradeoffs\n\nThis will give you strong material to speak in the interview.",
