    "content": "# PART D - S3 Deep Dive\n\n## 22. S3 concepts\n\n![S3 create event notification: event types/prefix/suffix area](https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20210316223233/Screenshot94.png)\n\n- Shows the event notification creation form where event name, prefix, suffix, and event types are configured.\n- Use prefix/suffix filters to avoid triggering on the wrong files.\n- Separate incoming/ and processed/ prefixes to avoid recursive Lambda triggers.\n- S3 event notification is common for document/image processing pipelines.\n\nS3 is object storage, not a file system.\n\n| Concept | Meaning |\n| --- | --- |\n| Bucket | top-level container |\n| Object | file/data with key and metadata |\n| Key | object path-like name |\n| Prefix | logical grouping using key prefix |\n| Versioning | keeps multiple object versions |\n| Lifecycle | transition/delete objects automatically |\n| Multipart upload | upload large objects in parts |\n| Pre-signed URL | temporary access URL |\n\n### Object key example\n\n```text\ns3://company-docs/raw/customer_id=123/date=2026-06-18/invoice.pdf\n```\n\n### Upload file with boto3\n\n```python\nimport boto3\n\ns3 = boto3.client(\"s3\")\ns3.upload_file(\"invoice.pdf\", \"my-bucket\", \"raw/invoice.pdf\")\n```\n\n### Download file\n\n```python\ns3.download_file(\"my-bucket\", \"raw/invoice.pdf\", \"/tmp/invoice.pdf\")\n```\n\n### Put object from bytes\n\n```python\ns3.put_object(\n    Bucket=\"my-bucket\",\n    Key=\"processed/result.json\",\n    Body=b'{\"status\":\"ok\"}',\n    ContentType=\"application/json\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 23. S3 security\n\nChecklist:\n\n- Block public access unless explicitly needed.\n- Use bucket policies carefully.\n- Use IAM roles, not hardcoded keys.\n- Use KMS encryption where required.\n- Use pre-signed URLs for controlled temporary access.\n- Enable versioning for critical data.\n- Use lifecycle rules to control cost.\n- Log access when needed.\n\n### Pre-signed upload/download\n\n```python\nurl = s3.generate_presigned_url(\n    ClientMethod=\"get_object\",\n    Params={\"Bucket\": \"my-bucket\", \"Key\": \"raw/invoice.pdf\"},\n    ExpiresIn=900,\n)\n```\n\nUse case:\n\n```text\nFrontend asks API for upload URL\nAPI validates user and returns pre-signed PUT URL\nFrontend uploads directly to S3\nS3 event starts processing\n```\n\nThis avoids sending large files through your API server.\n\n---\n\n## 24. S3 scaling and cost issues\n\n| Issue | Explanation | Fix |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Too many small files | Glue/Spark listing overhead, metadata overhead | compact files, partition better |\n| Incomplete multipart uploads | orphaned parts cost money | lifecycle rule to abort incomplete uploads |\n| Wrong storage class | unnecessary cost | lifecycle to IA/Glacier based on access |\n| Public bucket exposure | security incident | block public access, bucket policy review |\n| Same prefix hotspot concerns | less common now, but key design still matters | distribute workload logically |\n| Recursive events | runaway Lambda invocations | separate input/output prefixes |\n| Large file through API Gateway | size/time limits | pre-signed S3 upload |\n\n---",
    "searchText": "aws lead source expansion d - s3 deep dive part d - s3 deep dive 22. s3 concepts ! s3 create event notification: event types/prefix/suffix area https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20210316223233/screenshot94.png - shows the event notification creation form where event name, prefix, suffi... # part d - s3 deep dive ## 22. s3 concepts ![s3 create event notification: event types/prefix/suffix area](https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20210316223233/screenshot94.png) - shows the event notification creation form where event name, prefix, suffix, and event types are configured. - use prefix/suffix filters to avoid triggering on the wrong files. - separate incoming/ and processed/ prefixes to avoid recursive lambda triggers. - s3 event notification is common for document/image processing pipelines. s3 is object storage, not a file system. | concept | meaning | | --- | --- | | bucket | top-level container | | object | file/data with key and metadata | | key | object path-like name | | prefix | logical grouping using key prefix | | versioning | keeps multiple object versions | | lifecycle | transition/delete objects automatically | | multipart upload | upload large objects in parts | | pre-signed url | temporary access url | ### object key example ```text s3://company-docs/raw/customer_id=123/date=2026-06-18/invoice.pdf ``` ### upload file with boto3 ```python import boto3 s3 = boto3.client(\"s3\") s3.upload_file(\"invoice.pdf\", \"my-bucket\", \"raw/invoice.pdf\") ``` ### download file ```python s3.download_file(\"my-bucket\", \"raw/invoice.pdf\", \"/tmp/invoice.pdf\") ``` ### put object from bytes ```python s3.put_object( bucket=\"my-bucket\", key=\"processed/result.json\", body=b'{\"status\":\"ok\"}', contenttype=\"application/json\" ) ``` --- ## 23. s3 security checklist: - block public access unless explicitly needed. - use bucket policies carefully. - use iam roles, not hardcoded keys. - use kms encryption where required. - use pre-signed urls for controlled temporary access. - enable versioning for critical data. - use lifecycle rules to control cost. - log access when needed. ### pre-signed upload/download ```python url = s3.generate_presigned_url( clientmethod=\"get_object\", params={\"bucket\": \"my-bucket\", \"key\": \"raw/invoice.pdf\"}, expiresin=900, ) ``` use case: ```text frontend asks api for upload url api validates user and returns pre-signed put url frontend uploads directly to s3 s3 event starts processing ``` this avoids sending large files through your api server. --- ## 24. s3 scaling and cost issues | issue | explanation | fix | | --- | --- | --- | | too many small files | glue/spark listing overhead, metadata overhead | compact files, partition better | | incomplete multipart uploads | orphaned parts cost money | lifecycle rule to abort incomplete uploads | | wrong storage class | unnecessary cost | lifecycle to ia/glacier based on access | | public bucket exposure | security incident | block public access, bucket policy review | | same prefix hotspot concerns | less common now, but key design still matters | distribute workload logically | | recursive events | runaway lambda invocations | separate input/output prefixes | | large file through api gateway | size/time limits | pre-signed s3 upload | ---"
