    "content": "# PART M - Security Checklist\n\n## 49. AWS security checklist\n\n| Area | Checklist |\n| --- | --- |\n| IAM | least privilege, roles, no long-lived keys |\n| S3 | block public access, bucket policies, encryption |\n| KMS | correct key policy and rotation requirements |\n| Secrets | use Secrets Manager/SSM, not hardcoded secrets |\n| Network | private subnets for DBs, SG least access |\n| API | auth, throttling, validation, WAF if public |\n| Logs | avoid sensitive data in logs |\n| CloudTrail | enabled for audit |\n| CI/CD | scan dependencies, restrict deploy permissions |\n| Data | lifecycle, backups, retention |\n\n### Secrets in Python\n\nBad:\n\n```python\nDB_PASSWORD = \"hardcoded-password\"\n```\n\nBetter:\n\n```python\nimport boto3\nimport json\n\nsecrets = boto3.client(\"secretsmanager\")\nresponse = secrets.get_secret_value(SecretId=\"prod/db\")\nsecret = json.loads(response[\"SecretString\"])\n```\n\n---",
